                                Neapolitan language was the <i>de facto</i> official language of the sovereign state.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                After the Italian unification, Naples became a part of the unified Italy in 1861.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Naples was hit by number of severe epidemics in 19<sup>th</sup> century, and this caused huge 
                                immigration waves to United States and South America <i>(especially to Argentina)</i>. 
                            </p>
                            <p>
